Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.03,0:06:21.07,Default,,0,0,21,,{\frx286}Like being quick to cry.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.90,0:06:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\move(960,1024,2100,1024,640,860)}Cooking!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:22.74,0:06:22.78,Default,,0,0,-44,,Piece o' cake!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:22.78,0:06:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Piece o' cake!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:23.70,0:06:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll stir up somethin' up for y'all scumbags!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:26.45,0:06:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\move(960,1024,1859,1024,920,1030)}Entertaining guests.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:27.70,0:06:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Say "ho"!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:30.12,0:06:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Say "ho"!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:31.29,0:06:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}This is no good! You're slipping further \Nand further from femininity!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:32.62,0:06:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Say "ho"!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:34.04,0:06:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}What the hell kinda ideas \Ndo you have about me?!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:36.67,0:06:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}One thing girls often do \Nis harp on about past incidents.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:40.88,0:06:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, okay. That I can do.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:47.22,0:06:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's happening!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.80,0:06:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A long time ago...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:49.72,0:06:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got something!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:51.06,0:06:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,...in the third year of elementary school,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:53.02,0:06:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hisamochi put eraser shavings in my school lunch.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:57.40,0:06:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll never forgive him.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:59.07,0:07:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it! Keep going!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.78,0:07:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}When I was in kindergarten, \NI was cast as a fairy in the school play.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:06.03,0:07:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}But on the day of the performance, \NI had a fever and had to stay home.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:09.16,0:07:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Always the same story.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:10.70,0:07:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Always a victim of bad luck.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.70,0:07:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to be a fairy, dammit!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:15.33,0:07:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}This is less like feminine complaining \Nand more like drunken muttering.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:18.58,0:07:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}He's harping on about past incidents alright, \Nbut he seems more like an old guy in a pub.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.30,0:07:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is so rude.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:26.26,0:07:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody understands me.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.76,0:07:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I judge the defendant just about ladylike.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:32.26,0:07:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Please continue.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.43,0:07:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}When I was three years old, my mom blamed me \Nfor breaking a vase when it was the cat's fault.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:38.27,0:07:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what I said, she wouldn't listen.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.36,0:07:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-You've got a good memory.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:42.44,0:07:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Three days after I was born!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:44.11,0:07:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}While holding me, the nurse surreptitiously \Nswitched me for the baby next to me.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:51.24,0:07:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Swine of a duke! How dare you, Pierre!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.33,0:07:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This is unforgivable!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:55.62,0:07:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, after me!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:57.62,0:07:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,To the Bastille!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:00.00,0:08:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Marii's regressed to a former life!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:02.21,0:08:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe this {\i1}is{\i0} ladylike.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.50,0:08:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:04.71,0:08:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Captain of the Imperial Guard, \Nliving in 18th century Paris!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.47,0:08:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So you were a guy in your past life? Figures.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:11.72,0:08:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}What about trying the complete \Nopposite of manly behaviour?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:14.81,0:08:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:15.81,0:08:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Hmm, they say the manly pursuits \Nare drinking, spending, and partying.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:19.27,0:08:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Drinking, spending, and partying?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.73,0:08:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That suits Marii to a T.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.90,0:08:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty cool!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:24.11,0:08:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Aren't I supposed to do the exact opposite?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:26.65,0:08:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,By "opposite", you mean...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:28.57,0:08:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Eating, scrounging, and working?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.78,0:08:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This suits Marii to a T as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:33.83,0:08:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, but I wouldn't really call it ladylike.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:36.25,0:08:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Some ladies live like that, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:38.21,0:08:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one option.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:39.42,0:08:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Marii, let's take a bath.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:42.00,0:08:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll get us all the proof we need.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:00.06,0:09:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to say...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:01.44,0:09:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, I'd say neither "man" nor "woman" fits you.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:03.98,0:09:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But "child" is perfect.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.45,0:09:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Asakusa!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.99,0:09:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's a big-ass lantern.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:13.28,0:09:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like this is gonna be a blessed day.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:16.16,0:09:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}The Kaminarimon gate and the lantern \Nwere donated in 1960 by Konosuke Matsushita.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:28.13,0:09:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There sure are a lot of foreigners here.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:30.67,0:09:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess this is a sight you can only see in Japan.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.34,0:09:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The Balinese Kecak dance was developed by a German.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:36.60,0:09:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:37.72,0:09:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I love how red this thing is.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:40.77,0:09:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The red of Campari originally came from crushed insects.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:44.19,0:09:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Why do you keep answering with \Nvaguely related facts that are hard to respond to?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:47.94,0:09:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Finding out is a moment of embarrassment, \Nbut never knowing is a lifetime of shame.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:51.32,0:09:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be perfectly fine with never knowing these things.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.86,0:09:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Yeah, but Kaminarimon's been around for ages, \Neven if it hasn't always looked like this.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:58.33,0:10:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's all good. Let's go!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.00,0:10:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Kaminarimon really is the ideal gate.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:06.96,0:10:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't the Arc de Triomphe more popular worldwide?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.96,0:10:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Très bien!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:11.42,0:10:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There's also the Brandenburg Gate in Berlin.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:13.93,0:10:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Prost!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:16.68,0:10:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor old Kaminarimon.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:19.14,0:10:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Yeah, but a gate has to lead into a building. \NThat's what they're for!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:23.31,0:10:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Where do you end up if you go through \Nthe Arc de Triomphe and the Brandenblah Gate?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:28.48,0:10:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:29.90,0:10:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Kaminarimon leads to Sensouji Temple...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:32.24,0:10:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}The Arc de Triomphe isn't so much in front of \Nsomething as behind or after something.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:36.87,0:10:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,After?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:37.74,0:10:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Originally, after winning a victory,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:40.62,0:10:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}armies would march through the gate as \Na celebration or to mark the anniversary.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:46.50,0:10:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So... that was enough to make them happy?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:49.21,0:10:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Just... passing through the gate?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:50.80,0:10:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}It reminds me of those gates they have \Nto enter and exit a sports festival.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:01.31,0:11:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}In other words, it makes you feel like \Nyou're done and you can have a rest?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:03.81,0:11:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I suppose so.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:05.44,0:11:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds kind of anticlimactic.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:08.44,0:11:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess it depends on how you're feeling.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:10.61,0:11:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hey. Shall we take a photo together?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:13.49,0:11:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, good idea!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.70,0:11:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are people covering themselves in smoke?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:22.08,0:11:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They say that the smoke will help fix your bad points.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:25.83,0:11:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Bad points, eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:30.25,0:11:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I don't need to do it.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:32.13,0:11:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There ain't nothing wrong with me.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:34.59,0:11:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Saying that is a sign of a bad character.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:37.34,0:11:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you said it leaves a lot to be desired, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:39.30,0:11:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have poor fashion sense.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:40.68,0:11:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What the—
Dialogue: 10,0:11:40.68,0:11:41.97,Alt,,0,0,0,,I don't think—
Dialogue: 10,0:11:43.06,0:11:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think—
Dialogue: 10,0:11:43.06,0:11:44.35,Alt,,0,0,0,,What the—
Dialogue: 10,0:11:45.31,0:11:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus your timing is terrible.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:47.52,0:11:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,She's watching us very awkwardly.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.77,0:11:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it, I get it! I'll put my head in the stupid smoke!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.21,0:12:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}So how do you pronounce it? \NSensouji or Asakusa Temple?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:15.80,0:12:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is right?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:16.97,0:12:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensouji.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:18.05,0:12:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But the station is called Asakusa. Isn't that confusing?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:20.59,0:12:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's Kaminarimon when you'd expect it to be Raimon.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.43,0:12:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like, sort your pronunciation out.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:26.68,0:12:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Temples are almost always "ji", though.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.81,0:12:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Akihabara and Akibahara are confusing, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:32.02,0:12:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Akibahara is actually the original pronunciation.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.78,0:12:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Nowadays people shorten it to Akiba.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:37.40,0:12:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Kichijouji is also kind of complicated.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.32,0:12:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}If you remove the last character, it'd be "kisshou", \Nbut for some reason, if you add "ji" it becomes "kichijou".
Dialogue: 10,0:12:43.95,0:12:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Likewise, if you remove the last character \Nfrom Kokubunji, it would be "kokubu".
Dialogue: 10,0:12:46.58,0:12:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But you add "ji" and suddenly it's "kokubun".
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.75,0:12:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Kisshou and Kokubun are just fine!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:50.83,0:12:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They should make up their damn minds!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:52.21,0:12:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate it when things aren't clear.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:54.75,0:12:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we go make things clear?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:01.55,0:13:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Number 64!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.14,0:13:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Unlucky?!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:05.76,0:13:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,How'd you guys do?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.39,0:13:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a slighty lucky!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.85,0:13:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.73,0:13:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Unlucky.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:13.19,0:13:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you, Kukuru?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:14.94,0:13:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Very unlucky.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:15.90,0:13:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.19,0:13:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}"The person you await will never arrive", \N"Your engagement will be broken off",
Dialogue: 10,0:13:21.24,0:13:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}"Lost items will never be found", \N"Illness will persist",
Dialogue: 10,0:13:24.49,0:13:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}"Business will be poor", \N"Travel will be postponed"...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:29.71,0:13:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything's going to go poorly!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.33,0:13:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't sweat it!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.83,0:13:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Sensouji is famous for giving out \Na lot of unlucky fortunes.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.55,0:13:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Isn't making people feel crappy \Nthe opposite of what a temple should do?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.59,0:13:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}It's not so much that as helping people \Nbe careful before they make any mistakes.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:45.97,0:13:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.22,0:13:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you get, Teto?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:53.40,0:13:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Very lucky?!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.77,0:13:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No fair!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:55.52,0:13:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Typical! She's always been like that!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:58.57,0:14:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Her luck is impossibly good!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.36,0:14:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}"Your wishes will come true", \N"Business will thrive",
Dialogue: 10,0:14:04.82,0:14:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}"The person you await will arrive soon", \N"You will overcome any conflict"...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.12,0:14:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't get the luck if you don't work hard for it.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:15.08,0:14:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not a sure thing!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:16.59,0:14:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Fine, then why don't you share \Nsome of that good luck around?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:20.84,0:14:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:24.55,0:14:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Tastes so much better when it's free!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:27.93,0:14:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a very Marii thing to say.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:29.60,0:14:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So sharing good luck means treating you to a drink?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:32.31,0:14:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't sweat it! "Your business will thrive", y'know!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:36.27,0:14:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope all your other predictions come true, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:39.11,0:14:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! I'm sure they won't!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:41.78,0:14:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are your tripe stew and miso cucumber!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:44.95,0:14:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It came true!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:45.99,0:14:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}It's not an awaited person, but it's definitely \Nsomething we were waiting for.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:48.20,0:14:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you dropped this, miss.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:51.12,0:14:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The lost item!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.12,0:14:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's "very lucky" for you!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:53.62,0:14:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And it seems to have transferred to you!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:55.96,0:14:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.92,0:15:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,O Lucky One, grant me good fortune!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:00.59,0:15:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think it works like that!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:07.14,0:15:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But... it {\i1}does{\i0} look like you've been blessed from above.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:19.73,0:15:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as if she were a shoreline protected by tetrapods.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.74,0:15:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,She always comes out of any situation unscathed.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.28,0:15:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What's her secret?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:31.99,0:15:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Gah, so itchy.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:33.37,0:15:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What's up? Got crabs?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:36.12,0:15:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that for?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:37.83,0:15:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Mosquito.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:38.33,0:15:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Mosquito?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:39.17,0:15:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone left the window open.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:51.05,0:15:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Mosquito.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:53.72,0:15:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, now—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.39,0:15:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\clip(m 850.5 954 b 865.5 960 885 969 900 976.5 939 996 1000.5 1030.5 1014 1044 l 1164 1033.5 1171.5 942)}Ah, now—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.47,0:15:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\clip(m 802.5 946.5 l 918 951 b 915 960 909 976.5 910.5 990 918 1014 922.5 1042.5 927 1060.5 l 754.5 1029)}Ah, now—
Dialogue: 11,0:15:54.64,0:15:54.68,Default,,255,145,108,,{\fry328\frx34\bord0\blur3\clip(m 915 915 l 1114.5 904.5 b 1120.5 930 1156.5 961.5 1176 972 l 895.5 1008)}Ah, now—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.64,0:15:54.68,Default,,255,145,108,,{\fry328\frx34\1a&H80&\blur3\clip(m 915 915 l 1114.5 904.5 b 1120.5 930 1156.5 961.5 1176 972 l 895.5 1008)}Ah, now—
Dialogue: 11,0:15:54.68,0:15:54.73,Default,,400,0,185,,{\fry322\frx52\bord0\blur1.5}Ah, now—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.68,0:15:54.73,Default,,400,0,185,,{\fry322\frx52\1a&H80&\blur1.5}Ah, now—
Dialogue: 11,0:15:54.73,0:15:54.77,Default,,469,-69,214,,{\fry322\frx56\bord0\blur1.5\clip(m 1138.5 811.5 l 1299 816 b 1287 838.5 1267.5 883.5 1260 907.5 l 1105.5 874.5)}Ah, now—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.73,0:15:54.77,Default,,469,-69,214,,{\fry322\frx56\1a&H80&\blur1.5\clip(m 1138.5 811.5 l 1299 816 b 1287 838.5 1267.5 883.5 1260 907.5 l 1105.5 874.5)}Ah, now—
Dialogue: 11,0:15:54.77,0:15:54.81,Default,,569,-169,204,,{\fry316\frx62\bord0\blur1.5\clip(m 1138.5 811.5 l 1342.5 816 b 1336.5 856.5 1293 912 1293 933 l 1105.5 874.5)}Ah, now—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.77,0:15:54.81,Default,,569,-169,204,,{\fry316\frx62\1a&H80&\blur1.5\clip(m 1138.5 811.5 l 1342.5 816 b 1336.5 856.5 1293 912 1293 933 l 1105.5 874.5)}Ah, now—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.81,0:15:54.85,Default,,612,-212,173,,{\fry314\frx58\blur3\clip(m 1138.5 811.5 l 1357.5 820.5 b 1336.5 868.5 1293 912 1300.5 940.5 l 1105.5 874.5)}Ah, now—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:57.27,0:15:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A feint, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:59.44,0:16:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I dunno if this is still 'bout mosquitoes or what,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:01.52,0:16:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}but nobody smacks me around \Nand gets away with it.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.70,0:16:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\q2}Her skills have much improved \Nsince last time. This won't be easy.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:16.54,0:16:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The first to make a move will lose.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:25.21,0:16:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That itches!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:26.26,0:16:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}"The first to make a move will lose", my ass! \NWe both lost in the end!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:31.30,0:16:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No fair! It bit me while I was sleeping!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:34.56,0:16:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,How come only one of us was spared?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:36.68,0:16:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm? Oh, I wonder!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.35,0:16:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A draft?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:41.52,0:16:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The airflow is different over there.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.98,0:16:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Even if a mosquito tried to make its way over there, \Nthe draft would push it somewhere else.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:49.45,0:16:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So {\i1}that's{\i0} why she wasn't bitten?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:51.78,0:16:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always been like this.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:53.91,0:16:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Fall, fall, snow, snow!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.12,0:16:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Fall, fall, hail, hail!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:01.29,0:17:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if everyone else around her suffered,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:06.59,0:17:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,she'd somehow always come out unscathed.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:10.30,0:17:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, we're gonna be late!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:23.19,0:17:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Due to a signal failure, we are temporarily \Nsuspending service on this line.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:38.08,0:17:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}One way or another, she's always \Nbeen blessed with good fortune.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:40.75,0:17:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be so silly!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:43.21,0:17:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! It's vertical!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:44.46,0:17:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just superstition!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.75,0:17:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Five hundred yen notes are rare!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:49.51,0:17:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's got five hundred yen all the same!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:57.10,0:17:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe this!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:58.60,0:18:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The wall just suddenly falling?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:00.56,0:18:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,'Scuse me, ladies!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:01.85,0:18:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2\q}There'll be some disruption \Nwhile I put up the soundproofin'.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:05.31,0:18:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do the gods love her so much?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:08.90,0:18:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's just that the devil loves us.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:13.99,0:18:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's just that my usual behaviour is so good.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:16.49,0:18:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Usual behaviour?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:18.58,0:18:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this? You some stalker or something?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:20.79,0:18:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, who are you calling a stalker?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.41,0:18:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}These are pics I took of Tetora \Ngoing about her business.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.88,0:18:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}If we study these, we'll be able to ape \Nwhatever worthy behaviour she's doing.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:28.46,0:18:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Use her as a model, you mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:31.38,0:18:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}But she's not really doing any \Nparticularly good deeds in these pics.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:35.55,0:18:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I don't buy it, not for a second! She's gotta be doing \N{\i1}something{\i0} to have the gods on her side!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.27,0:18:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this for example!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:41.31,0:18:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,She's just watching TV.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:43.48,0:18:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope. Look closer. It's an old analogue TV.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:46.31,0:18:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone in the world's switched to digital.
Comment: 9,0:18:48.15,0:18:53.57,Alt,,50,350,28,,{\an7\fs48\shad0}Note:
Comment: 9,0:18:48.15,0:18:53.57,Alt,,50,350,78,,{\an7\fs44\bord4\shad0\q2}Mascot characters supporting (Chidejika) \Nand opposing (Analoguma) the switch to digital.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:48.23,0:18:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Chidejika {地デジカ }and Analoguma {アナログマ }have been relieved of duty.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:51.11,0:18:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Analoguma didn't really do his duty, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:53.70,0:18:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Chidejika must have gotten tired of \Ngetting in and out of that swimsuit he wears.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:57.28,0:18:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You're thinking of someone else.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:58.78,0:19:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Forget all this digital talk.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:02.29,0:19:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}The key here is the disposition that \Nallows her to put up with this old analogue tuner.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.58,0:19:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, we must treasure what we have.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.67,0:19:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that worthy behaviour?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:09.75,0:19:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:11.21,0:19:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got that TV here.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:12.76,0:19:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You stole it?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:13.80,0:19:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Is my reputation {\i1}that{\i0} bad?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:15.59,0:19:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I got permission, don't you worry.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:17.59,0:19:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}My TV? Sure! It probably doesn't \Nhave much longer anyway.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:20.14,0:19:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Now we just watch this and \Nwait for the divine blessings to roll in.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:26.56,0:19:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:27.56,0:19:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't feel very blessed!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:30.61,0:19:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So it finally broke, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:34.07,0:19:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}About a week ago it started making \Nthis weird buzzing sound.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:41.03,0:19:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Who in their right mind would bring that 'ere?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:43.12,0:19:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to stop her.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:44.83,0:19:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:46.04,0:19:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}So... by all rights, it should have \Nblown up at Tetora's place?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:52.09,0:19:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What kind of abnormal ability is this?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:54.97,0:19:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sticking with you from now on.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.30,0:20:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Right behind you is the safest place to be.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:01.39,0:20:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.39,0:20:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll follow suit, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:05.31,0:20:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:07.52,0:20:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, guess I'm the butt.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.98,0:20:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Weirdos.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:11.40,0:20:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Oh! Teto moved!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:13.32,0:20:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've gotta do the same.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:14.82,0:20:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Kigu, who's standing behind Tetora, moved.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:16.70,0:20:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've gotta do the same.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:17.95,0:20:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\q2}Gan, who's standing behind Kigu, \Nwho's standing behind Tetora, moved.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:21.28,0:20:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've gotta do the same.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:22.74,0:20:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\q2}Kukuru, who's standing behind Gankyou, who's standing \Nbehind Kigu, who's standing behind Tetora, moved.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:26.25,0:20:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've gotta do the same.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:28.00,0:20:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Gotta do the same!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:42.51,0:20:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:45.10,0:20:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so fresh!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:48.81,0:20:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Rakugo breakdancing! It's something new!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:27.60,0:21:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This is crap!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:28.93,0:21:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Do some bloody rakugo!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:29.89,0:21:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They hate it...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:31.27,0:21:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This is terrible.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:32.02,0:21:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Where the hell is Tetora?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:33.98,0:21:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Apparently, her train broke down, so she got a taxi, \Nbut the road was closed because of a sinkhole.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:39.57,0:21:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of abnormal ability is this?!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:43.20,0:21:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,See? She always comes out unscathed.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:46.37,0:21:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as if she were protected by tetrapods.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:50.21,0:21:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry I couldn't make it!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:51.62,0:21:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought a watermelon as an apology.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:54.08,0:21:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Watermelon!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:55.46,0:21:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I got an imported one because it was cheaper.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:58.51,0:22:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go fetch a knife.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:41.02,0:23:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Gankyou Kuurubiyuutei here.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:43.69,0:23:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}You have our eternal gratitude \Nfor your continued patronage.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:48.37,0:23:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Formal announcements always make me nervous.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:52.29,0:23:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I don't understand people who can just \Nblabber away in front of strangers all day!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:56.16,0:23:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They must have nerves of steel.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.29,0:24:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}At any rate, here's what's in \Nthe fourth episode of Rakugo Girls:
Dialogue: 10,0:24:02.84,0:24:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}"Glasses Girl", "A Good Day to Daiba", \Nand "Eye of the Bunny".
